The problem if I declare 

```typescript
getData(): MVCArray<LatLng | WeightedLocation>;
```
is that we can not write the following :

```typescript
// Equals property is missing in WeightedLocation
let datas: google.maps.MVCArray<google.maps.LatLng> = heatmap.getData(); 
```
we have to do

```typescript
let datas = heatmap.getData();
(<google.maps.LatLng>datas.getAt(0)).lat();
```

I hesitated but I though it was better to do 
```typescript
let datas = heatmap.getData<google.maps.LatLng>();
datas.getAt(0).lat();
```
with the big drawback that it's a breaking change and can be  legitimately refused by DefinitelyTyped community :)

